r by its path??  so far we pretty much assumed that name == path, but it could be not the case. @mih -- did you have such setups by any chance?\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n(git)hopa:/tmp/datasets.datalad.org/neurovault[master]git\r\n$> git submodule add --name nidm $PWD/../nidm nidm-path \r\nCloning into '/tmp/datasets.datalad.org/neurovault/nidm-path'...\r\ndone.\r\ncached/staged changes:                                                           \r\n .gitmodules | 3 +++\r\n nidm-path   | 1 +\r\n\r\n$> python -c 'from datalad.api import Dataset; print Dataset(\".\").get_subdatasets()'         \r\n[u'nidm-path', u'snapshots']\r\ncached/staged changes:                                                           \r\n .gitmodules | 3 +++\r\n nidm-path   | 1 +\r\n\r\n$> cat .gitmodules \r\n[submodule \"archive\"]\r\n\tpath = snapshots\r\n\turl = ./archive\r\n[submodule \"nidm\"]\r\n\tpath = nidm-path\r\n\turl = /tmp/datasets.datalad.org/neurovault/../nidm\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1081/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1081/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}